5.1 Elfeed Integration
======================

Elfeed is a popular RSS feed reader for Emacs.  Instapapier provides
direct integration to save feed entries to Instapaper.

5.1.1 Setting Up Elfeed
-----------------------

First, install and configure elfeed:

     (use-package elfeed
       :ensure t
       :config
       (setq elfeed-feeds
             '("https://planet.emacslife.com/atom.xml"
               "https://sachachua.com/blog/feed/")))

5.1.2 Adding Elfeed Entries to Instapaper
-----------------------------------------

In the elfeed search buffer, place your cursor on an entry and run:

     M-x instapapier-add-elfeed-entry-at-point

   *Suggested configuration:*

     (use-package elfeed
       :ensure t
       :bind (:map elfeed-search-mode-map
                   ("i" . instapapier-add-elfeed-entry-at-point))
       :config
       (setq elfeed-feeds
             '("https://planet.emacslife.com/atom.xml"
               "https://sachachua.com/blog/feed/")))

   Now you can press ‘i’ on any entry in elfeed to save it to
Instapaper.


